[Bovine brucellosis (caused by _Brucella abortus_) has caused devastating losses to farmers in the United States over the last century. Collaborative efforts of the U.S. Department of Agriculture, the livestock industries, and State animal health authorities achieved brucellosis-free status in 48 states with no known infection in 2002.

The only known focus of _Brucella abortus_ infection left in the nation is in bison and elk, which originally acquired the infection from cattle. According to the superficial description of the research, these introductions were of different sources in Wyoming and Idaho. Unfortunately, the study has not yet been published to allow assessment of whether the conclusions posited are supported by the data.

The bacterium became established in these wildlife species and does not currently pose a threat for their populations. However, it does represent a big concern for domestic livestock. - Mod.PMB

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3123696,228.]
